tcher was then transferred to sunderland for £ million he joined sheffield wednesday on  july  fletcher played for the scotland under team that finished runners up to spain in the  european championship he has since represented scotland at full international level and in  became the first player since  to score a hattrick for scotland contents  early life  club career  hibernian  burnley  wolverhampton wanderers  sunderland  marseille loan  sheffield wednesday  international career  career statistics  club  international goals  honours  club  individual  references  external links early lifeedit fletcher who was born in shrewsbury shropshire spent much of his early years living on british army bases in england and germany where his liverpudlian soldier father kenny fletcher was based his father died from cancer aged  when fletcher was aged only  prompting his scottish mother mary to relocate him and his younger sister bree to hamilton south lanarkshire to be closer to her family hibernian youth coach john park also from hamilton spotted his footballing talent and the youngster joined the leith clubs youth network aged  club careeredit hibernianedit fletcher made his debut for hibs on  april  replacing garry oconnor for the final eight minutes in a – scottish premier league win over kilmarnock at easter road he totalled five appearances that season making his first start on  may in the final fixture a – loss at livingston he became a first team regular in the – season playing  times and scoring five goals his first goal came on  october set up by oconnor to conclude a – home win over dundee united on  march as a stminute substitute for scott brown he scored twice in a – win at dunfermline athletic also assisting one of derek riordans brace in the – season fletcher scored  goals in just  minutes on the pitch which approximated to a goal every other game he took on a more prominent role in the – season after hibs had sold star strikers oconnor and derek riordan fletcher scored in hibernians – intertoto cup win over dinaburg and played regularly during the league season the highlight of the season for fletcher and hibs was when he scored two goals in the – win over kilmarnock in the  league cup final fletcher became hibs main striker during the – season he scored his first professional hattrick in a – win over gretna and won the scottish football writers young player of the year award fletcher was touted for a move to real madrid due to madrids scouts watching him after he performed well for scotlands youth teams the daily mail reported in november  that manchester city and two other premier league teams were interested in signing fletcher and the daily record reported on  january  that middlesbrough were preparing a £ million offer towards the end of the january transfer window hibs rejected an approach from celtic fletcher then publicly pleaded for hibs to agree a deal with celtic arguing for the development of my career it is time to move to a bigger club but hibs refused to sell him fletcher finished the season by being voted the scottish football writers young player of the season again burnleyedit on  june  burnley offered £ million for fletcher a few days later hibs accepted an offer of £ million plus incentives based on appearances for burnley fletcher completed the move when he agreed a fouryear contract with the lancashire club who paid a club record transfer fee to obtain his services after the move was completed former hibs striker keith wright questioned whether fletcher was ready to play in the premier league his first competitive goals for burnley came when he scored a brace in a – league cup win at hartlepool united on  august he scored his first goal in the premier league on  october against birmingham city fletcher was burnleys top goalscorer during the – season but the club were relegated from the premier league he was named burnley players player of the year for the season wolverhampton wanderersedit after burnley were relegated to the championship fletcher signed a fouryear contract with the option of a fifth year with premier league side wolverhampton wanderers on  june  he was transferred for around £ million which matched the wolves club record fletcher scored on his debut for wolves winning – against stoke city on the opening day of the season at molineux fletcher soon went on to get dropped from the first  as mick mccarthy decided to go with his previous successful –– formation with kevin doyle playing the lone striker role fletcher was mainly used as a substitute in the first half of the season but he still managed to pick up four goals these goals came against bolton wigan and two goals against tottenham in each fixture on  march  doyle tore a knee ligament while on international duty with ireland which kept him out of action for up to  weeks mccarthy was proved right by choosing fletcher to play the forward role as he went on to score five goals in five league games for the club his first goal came against fulham at molineux earning his side a – draw and his next came against birmingham scoring from the penalty spot to earn his side a – draw at st andrews his next two goals came against west bromwich albion at molineux in the black country derby earning his side a – win over their local rivals and getting them out of the bottom three fletcher grabbed his fifth goal for wolves against sunderland at the stadium of light again helping his side to a – win this saw fletcher reach  league goals by the end of the season  in all competitions fletcher began the – premier league season in similar fashion scoring a powerful header in the opening day victory against blackburn it was the second season running that fletcher had scored in the opening fixture of the season fletcher scored his second of the season against liverpool scoring after coming on as a substitute at half time he then scored both goals in a – win against sunderland despite fletcher scoring  goals during the league season wolves were relegated from the premier league fletcher submitted a transfer request on  august  after media reports linked sunderland with the player sunderlandedit fletcher right playing for sunderland against cardiff city in  on  august  wolves accepted an offer from sunderland of £ million fletcher signed a fouryear contract with sunderland he made his first appearance for sunderland in a – win against football league two club morecambe in the football league cup fletcher then scored his first two goals in his premier league debut for sunderland a – draw at swansea city he also scored once in each of his next three league matches against liverpool west ham united and wigan athletic fletchers excellent start to the season saw him win the barclays player of the month award for september after a spell of  games without a goal fletcher netted at craven cottage against fulham in a – sunderland victory he then went on to score in a – home win against reading and scored the only goal in a – win away against southampton fletcher then scored twice in a – win at wigan after a run of games without a win an injury sustained playing for scotland in march  ruled fletcher out for the rest of the – season fletcher was handed the number  shirt for the – season and returned to the bench for a – league cup win against milton keynes dons upon his premier league return after a sustained period of time out injured he came off the bench to score in the – defeat against crystal palace on  august on  september fletcher was ruled out for four to six weeks with a shoulder injury the result of a heavy fall during the previous weeks match against west brom fletcher scored his second goal of the season on  october  netting the first in a – win against local rivals newcastle united it was also sunderlands first win of the season on  december  fletcher scored his third goal of the season in a – draw against cardiff city he did not score again in the – season during which sunderland reached the league cup final and produced a late run of form to avoid relegation on  october  fletcher netted twice and assisted connor wickham in a – win against stoke city fletcher was at the double again almost a month later when he netted twice against crystal palace at selhurst park his fifth goal of the season came on the last day of the season on  may  where he scored a header to open the scoring in a – defeat away to chelsea on  august  fletcher scored a consolation goal for sunderland in their – defeat away to leicester city at the king power stadium on  october  fletcher scored the opening goal in sunderlands – draw against west ham united on  october  fletcher scored the third and final goal of the match in the tyne–wear derby against archrivals newcastle in a – win marseille loanedit on  february  fletcher joined ligue  side marseille on loan until the end of the season he made his debut for the club six days later coming on as a secondhalf substitute for michy batshuayi in a – loss to rivals paris saintgermain in le classique at the stade vélodrome on  february fletcher made his full debut in a – coupe de france win at fourthtier amateur side trélissac setting up romain alessandrini for the first goal before netting himself in the th minute sheffield wednesdayedit following his release from sunderland fletcher joined sheffield wednesday on a free transfer on  july  international careeredit fletcher was eligible to represent either england his birthplace and the nation of his father or scotland his mothers home country and his place of residence since the age of  he chose scotland fletcher was the top scorer in the scotland under team which reached the final of the  european championship losing to spain following the achievements of the under– side fletcher was named by the scotsman newspaper as one of the ten to watch in scottish sport during  fletcher made his debut for scotland under–s in the – season fletcher was named in the scotland squad for the first time in march  for a friendly match against croatia fletcher started the game and provided the assist for kenny miller to score the equalising goal in a – draw he was substituted at halftime due to injury he was dropped back to the under– team in september  but was immediately recalled to the full squad after scoring twice against slovenia under–s fletcher scored his first full international goal in a – win against iceland on  april  after being left out of euro  qualification matches against czech republic and spain fletcher publicly criticised head coach craig levein fletcher was then left out of the next scotland squad although levein claimed that this was because fletcher had not been playing regularly for his club side when levein attempted to select him for the squad in february  fletcher sent a text message stating that he did not want to join the squad the dispute continued through the remainder of  as levein insisted that fletcher would have to contact him first if he wanted to return to the squad his club manager mick mccarthy said in november  that fletcher wanted to play for scotland and that the situation should be resolved near the end of the – season levein advised the scottish media that he would not pick fletcher again following fletchers £ million move to sunderland in august  levein reiterated that fletcher would not feature for scotland again whilst he was manager levein also criticised the transfer fee paid by sunderland as quite obscene and claimed that fletcher had made no effort to rejoin the national squad the dispute came into further focus after fletcher performed well for sunderland and scotland only scored once in their first two  fifa world cup qualification matches fletcher stated on his twitter account that he would be willing to play for scotland his agent claimed that fletcher had made an attempt to reconcile with levein during in september  but nobody had provided details of how they could meet on  october  fletcher was recalled to the scotland squad for their world cup qualifiers with wales and belgium fletcher scored a hattrick for scotland in a – european qualifier victory over gibraltar at hampden park on  march  becoming the first player to score three in a match for the country since colin stein scored four against cyprus in  on  october away to the same opposition with both teams already eliminated he scored another treble in a – victory he became the fifth player to score more than one hattrick for scotland with the others being rs mccoll  robert hamilton  hughie gallacher  and denis law  career statisticsedit clubedit as of  april  season club league fa cup league cup europe total discipline apps goals apps goals apps goals apps goals apps goals hibernian –       – –     –       – –     –             –             –       – –     –             total             burnley –       – –     total             wolverhampton wanderers –       – –     –       – –     total             sunderland –       – –     –       – –     –       – –     –       – –     total             marseille –             total             sheffield wednesday –             career total             international goalsedit scores and results list scotlands goal tally first goal date venue opponent score result competition   april  hampden park glasgow scotland  iceland – –  fifa world cup qualification   march  hampden park glasgow scotland  gibraltar – – uefa euro  qualifying  –  –   october  hampden park glasgow scotland  poland – – uefa euro  qualifying   october  estádio algarve faro portugal  gibraltar – – uefa euro  qualifying  –  –   september  national stadium ta qali malta  malta – –  fifa world cup qualification honoursedit clubedit hibernian scottish league cup   sunderland football league cup runnerup – marseille coupe de france runnerup – individualedit sfwa young player of the year  – – spl young player of the month  october  august  february  october  march  premier league player of the month  